24/11/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The country's National Anti-corruption Department is investigating or plans to launch probes against three members of parliament, suspected of abuse of office and corruption, according to a statement from department chief Daniel Morar on Wednesday (23 November). Morar mentioned only one deputy by name -- Ion Dumitru -- a former manager of the national forestry firm Romsilva who is accused of causing damages of up to 2m euros to the state. (Nine o'clock - 23/11/05)
